  "text": "Grimes has apparently had no choice but to take to the social media platform owned by her ex-partner, Elon Musk, publicly pleading for his “immediate attention” regarding a “medical crisis” involving one of their children. In a post on X (formerly Twitter) on Thursday, Grimes wrote to Musk, “Plz respond about our child’s medical crisis. I am sorry to do this publicly but it is no longer acceptable to ignore this situation. This requires immediate attention.” “If you don’t want to talk to me can you please designate or hire someone who can so that we can more forward on solving this. This is urgent, Elon,” Grimes added. Responding to a fan in another post, Grimes wrote, “I’m not giving any details but he won’t respond to texts calls or emails and has skipped every meeting and our child will suffer life long impairment if he doesn’t respond asap, so I need him to fucking respond and if I have to apply public pressure then I guess that’s where we are at.” Grimes began dating Musk in 2018, and their on-again, off-again relationship lasted until 2022. They share three children and have been embroiled in a parental rights dispute over custody for the past year. Musk has yet to acknowledge Grimes’ posts—more disturbingly, it appears that he or someone at X may be shadow-banning them to limit their visibility.",
  "image": "https://consequence.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/grimes-elon-musk-break-up.jpg",
